Subject: range
Slot Definition: description
Quasi-formalism: ignore

Subject: gene annotation
Slot Definition: One of potentially many gene annotation terms to which the abbreviation denotes.
Quasi-formalism: Some abbreviation (a) denotes some GeneAnnotation (G) if and only if a refers to G.

Subject: ParcellationTerm
Slot Definition: One of potentially many parcellation terms (anatomical structures) which the abbreviation denotes.
Quasi-formalism: A denotes some PT

Subject: CellTypeTaxonomy
Slot Definition: The cell types taxonomy for which the cell type set is part of.
Quasi-formalism: CTS part_of_taxonomy CTT if and only if CTT is a taxonomy, and CTS is a member of CTT

Subject: CellTypeTaxon
Slot Definition: One of potentially many cell types taxons which together defines the cell type set.
Quasi-formalism: CTS contains_taxon CTT if and only if CTT is a part of CTS

Subject: CellTypeSet
Slot Definition: When the cell type set represents a taxonomic level, the parent is the next higher level in the heirarchy.
Quasi-formalism: CTS1 has_parent CTS2 if and only if CTS2 and CTS1 are part_of some CTT and CTS1 is_child_of CTS2

Subject: Abbreviation
Slot Definition: One of many abbreviation that are part of the cell type set name.
Quasi-formalism: CTT has_abbreviation some A if and only if CTT has_name some CTTN and A is part of CTTN

Subject: CellTypeTaxonomy
Slot Definition: The cell types taxonomy for which the cell type taxon is part of.
Quasi-formalism: CTT part_of_taxonomy CTTy if and only if CTT is a member of CTTy

Subject: Cluster
Slot Definition: One of potentially cell clusters which together defines the cell type taxon.
Quasi-formalism: CTT contains_cluster C if and only if C is a part of CTT

Subject: CellTypeTaxon
Slot Definition: When the taxonomy is a single inheritance tree, the parent represents the superclass for which the cell type taxon is a member of.
Quasi-formalism: CTT1 has_parent CTT2 if and only if CTT1 and CTT2 are_part_of some CTTy and CTT1 is_child_of CTT2

Subject: Abbreviation
Slot Definition: One of many abbreviation that are part of the cell type taxon name.
Quasi-formalism: CTT has_abbreviation some A if and only if CTT has_name some CTTN and A is part of CTTN

Subject: CellTypeTaxonomyCreationProcess
Slot Definition: The analysis process from which the cell types taxonomy was generated by.
Quasi-formalism: CTT was_generated_by CTTCP if and only if CTTCP has_output some CTT

Subject: ClusterSet
Slot Definition: One of potentially many input clusters set from which the cell type taxonomy is derived.
Quasi-formalism: CTT was_derived_from some CS if and only if CTT has_input some CS

Subject: CellTypeTaxonomy
Slot Definition: The previous version for which this cell type taxonomy is a revision of.
Quasi-formalism: CTT2 is_revision_of CTT1 if and only if CTT1 is a version of CTT2

Subject: ClusterSet
Slot Definition: One of potentially many input cluster sets from which the cell type taxonomy is derived.
Quasi-formalism: CTTCP used (involved_in) CS if and only if CS enables some process p', and p' is part of CTTCP.

Subject: ClusterSet
Slot Definition: The cluster set from which the cluster is part of.
Quasi-formalism: C part_of_set CS if and only if C part_of CS

Subject: ObservationRow
Slot Definition: One of potentially many input observations which together define the cluster.
Quasi-formalism: C contains_observation some O if and only if C has_input O

Subject: CellSpecimen
Slot Definition: One of potentially many sample which together define the cluster.
Quasi-formalism: C contains_sample CS if and only if CS part_of C

Subject: ObservationMatrix
Slot Definition: One of potentially many input observation matrices from which clusters are derived.
Quasi-formalism: CP used (involved_in) OB if and only if OB enables some process p', and p' is part of CP

Subject: ClusteringProcess
Slot Definition: The analysis process from which clusters was generated by.
Quasi-formalism: CS was_generated_by some CP if and only if CP is a process and CS was_output_of CP

Subject: ObservationMatrix
Slot Definition: One of potentially many input observation matrices from which clusters are derived.
Quasi-formalism: CS was_derived_from some OM if and only if CS has_input some OM

Subject: ClusterSet
Slot Definition: The previous version for which this clustering output is a revision of.
Quasi-formalism: CS2 is_revision_of CS1 if and only if CS1 is a version of CS2

Subject: CellTypeTaxonomy
Slot Definition: The cell types taxonomy for which the palette provides display color properties for.
Quasi-formalism: CP is_palette_for some CTT

Subject: ColorPalette
Slot Definition: The color palette for which the display color map is part of.
Quasi-formalism: DC part_of_palette CP if and only if DC is part_of CP

Subject: CellTypeTaxon
Slot Definition: The associated cell type taxon for the specified display color.
Quasi-formalism: DC is_color_for CTT if DC is associated with CTT

Subject: CellTypeSet
Slot Definition: The associated cell type set of the specified display color.
Quasi-formalism: DC is_color_for CTS if DC is associated with CTS

Subject: ObservationMatrixCreationProcess
Slot Definition: The aggregation process from which a observation matrix was generated by.
Quasi-formalism: OM was_generated_by some OMCP if and only if OMCP is a process and OM was_output_of OMCP

Subject: MatrixFile
Slot Definition: One of potentially matrix files which together represents the entire observation matrix.
Quasi-formalism: MF concretizes some OM

Subject: gene annotation
Slot Definition: One of set of genes which together forms the variable set of an observation matrix.

Subject: CellSpecimen
Slot Definition: One of many cell specimens from which observations in the matrix was derived from.
Quasi-formalism: OM was_derived_from some CSp if and only if OM has_input some CSp

Subject: ObservationMatrix
Slot Definition: The observation matrix for which is observation row is part of.
Quasi-formalism: OR part_of_matrix some OM if and only if OR part_of some OM

Subject: MatrixFile
Slot Definition: The specific file where this observation row is represented.
Quasi-formalism: OR represented in MF if and only if OR is part_of some OM and OM is_concretized_in some MF

Subject: CellSpecimen
Slot Definition: The cell specimen from which the observation was derived from.
Quasi-formalism: OR was_derived_from some CSp if and only if OR has_input some CSp
